  h2 
    a(NAME='requirements') Requirements 
    span(style='font-size: small;')
      a(href='#contents') Table of contents
  p For this demonstration, we want to build:
    ul
      li Two channels, a red channel and a green channel.
      li On each channel we will want to have three modes: Off, Blinking, and On.
      li Each channel should be independently switched between the three modes remotely or locally. 
      li In the Blink mode, the blink rate of each channel should be independently remotely controlled.
      li The LED intensity for each channel should be independently controlled locally but reported to the remote observer.
  hr
  h2 
    a(NAME='parts') Parts List 
    span(style='font-size: small;')
      a(href='#contents') Table of contents
  p We will use the 
    a(href='https://www.electrokit.com/en/', target='_blank') Elecktro:kit 
    | catalog for links to the descriptions to the products. Obtain:
    ul
      li A 
        a(href='https://www.electrokit.com/en/product/raspberry-pi-3-1gb-model-b-3/', target='_blank') Raspberry-Pi 3B 
        | or 
        a(href='https://www.electrokit.com/en/product/raspberry-pi-zero-wh-board-with-header-2/', target='_blank') Raspberry-Pi Zero WH
      li An 8GB (or greater) 
        a(href='https://www.electrokit.com/en/product/memory-card-microsdhc-8gb/', target='_blank') microSDHC Memory card 
        | for the Raspberry-Pi operating system
      li A 
        a(href='https://www.electrokit.com/en/product/power-supply-5v-2a-micro-usb-black/', target='_blank')  micro-USB 5V power supply 
        | to power the Raspberry-Pi
      li An 
        a(href='https://www.electrokit.com/en/product/arduino-uno-mega328-rev-3-2/', target='_blank') Arduino Uno
      li A 
        a(href='https://www.electrokit.com/en/product/usb-2-0-cable-a-male-b-male-1-8m/', target='_blank') USB 2.0 A-male to B-male cable 
        | to connect the Arduino Uno to the Raspberry-Pi
      li A 
        a(href='https://www.electrokit.com/en/product/solderless-breadboard-400-tie-points/', target='_blank') 82 x 55mm solderless breadboard with 400 tie points
      li
        a(href='https://www.electrokit.com/en/product/jumper-wires-1-pin-male-male-150mm-10-pack/', target='_blank') Breadboard jumper wires
      li
        a(href='https://www.electrokit.com/en/product/hook-up-wires-w-pins-for-breadboard/', target='_blank') Hook-up wires with pins for breadboard
      li Two  
        a(href='https://www.electrokit.com/en/product/resistor-carbon-film-0-25w-220ohm-220r/', target='_blank') 220 Ohm resistors
      li Two 
        a(href='https://www.electrokit.com/en/product/resistor-carbon-film-0-25w-10kohm-10k/', target='_blank') 10k Ohm resistors
      li Two 
        a(href='https://www.electrokit.com/en/product/trimmer-pot-pt-10-10kohm-horizontal/', target='_blank') 10k Ohm Single Turn trimmer pot
      li Two 
        a(href='https://www.electrokit.com/en/product/tryckknapp-pcb-12x12mm-4-pack-2/', target='_blank') PCB 12mm push buttons
      li One 
        a(href='https://www.electrokit.com/en/product/led-3mm-green-diffused-3500mcd/', target='_blank') Green LED
      li One 
        a(href='https://www.electrokit.com/en/product/led-3mm-red-diffused-3500mcd/', target='_blank') Red LED
  hr
  h2 
    a(NAME='construction') Constructing the Circuit 
    span(style='font-size: small;')
      a(href='#contents') Table of contents
  p Setup the microSD card and the Raspberry-Pi according to the 
    a(href='/tutorial/setupRPi', target='_blank') previous tutorial
    | . Build the following circuit with the above components. you can find the 
    a(href='http://fritzing.org/home/', target='_blank') Fritzing 
    | file 
    a(href='/img/tutorial/device-schemtatic.fzz', target='_blank') here
    | .
